In this case, animals may be excluded.
But even if the consciousness would not depend on the language, it would influence it so that the consciousness of the animals, created as a whole, would in many cases differ from most of our states of consciousness.
It is therefore difficult to explain how the consciousness of other animals works.
If that, as something interesting and subjective, is not allowed to be measured because it has the special hardware, nor is it allowed to be analyzed through our experiences, so your research presents us with great problems.
Most of my interventions refer to the content of the experience, but at the same time there is also one other aspect of the consciousness that would have to be easier for scientific research.
