Psychology of the overlaps: Why do we spend more money?
The auction participants are likely to spend more money and overvalue the product.
The neurologists and economists of the University of New York discovered the neurological - economic bases of this known and apparently irrational conduct.
According to the study in Science magazine, people don't want to lose in competitions like eBay auctions, so they prefer to pay even an excessive price.
Scientists tried to establish the neurological scheme of this "game" through experimental auctions.
One of the groups of volunteers played lottery, the other participated in an auction and in the meantime the active areas of the brain of the people participating in the experiment were examined through the functional magnetic resonance system (fMRI).
In both games the participants could make money, but during the auctions, where it is essential to bet more than the other, by losing the game the operation of the complex called stratum located under the cerebral cortex was intensified.
This area of the brain, in addition to many other functions, plays a role in the "self-reward" mechanism of the nervous system.
Thus, according to scientists, the increase in bets is explained as a prevention not to cause an intense reaction of the stratum.
To base his theory, the economists of the scientific group also carried out a financial follow-up study.
In this experiment three groups bet against one person under different circumstances.
The control group was simply informed of the actual value of the product in question, and its members bet.
Another group was also promised that if they win, they would receive 15 more dollars of prize.
On the other hand, the third group received exactly $15 before the auction, but in the event of a loss of the auction the members of the group lost even that money.
So the only difference between the two groups was that for one, the triumph was highlighted, and for the other, the failure.
However, by checking the hypothesis of neurologists, the members of the group who played "against failure" were willing to bet even more than the members of the control group and the "winning" group.
"These results cannot be deduced from any previously existing economic theory.
For those so far explained the phenomena of the auctions only with the joy of winning and with the prevention of the risks.
Only neurological visual methods helped resolve this contradiction between the two theories, so we now come to a third explanation "- said Andrew Schotter, professor of the Faculty of Economics at the University of New York.
Hepatitis: When should you go to the doctor?
In the world, some 500 million people suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, and in Hungary chronic liver disease is considered one of the main causes of death.
The number of people infected in this country is estimated at a hundred thousand, but only seven thousand are treated because many of the sick do not know that they are infected.
The name of hepatitis is the common name of different liver diseases caused by viruses.
Symptoms are very similar; liver infection and jaundice are characteristic, but their pathogens and caused diseases are very different.
Hepatitis viruses dependent on the pathogen are spread by two main forms: hepatitis A and E by food (for example with water or infected food), hepatitis B, C, D and other viruses with the blood and with body humors (sperm, vagina humor, saliva).
It is recommended that travellers protect themselves by means of a vaccine against the A and B virus, there are no vaccines against C.
Symptoms of hepatitis A appear two or three weeks after eating the infected food, it is manifested by general poor condition, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After that, jaundice appears on the skin and on the target of the eyes, excrement becomes clear, dark urine and healing can last even two - three weeks.
Annually one million people die in the world from cancer and liver cirrhosis caused by hepatitis B, the most serious forms of this disease.
The main reason for this is that according to the calculations, only one in ten infected people receive pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: without treatment it can cause liver cirrhosis and even cancer.
Most of the infected people do not know that they are ill because this pathological agent gradually destroys the liver cells and often the first symptoms only appear 20-30 years later.
Premature recognition, systematic medical monitoring, is therefore very important.
This disease is much more common in three groups: people who had blood transfusion before 1991, drug users and those who wear tattoos.
There are currently about 200 million people in the world who suffer from chronic hepatitis C.
As this disease can be discovered with routine laboratory control as well, it is worth consulting with the family doctor when you experience some unknown symptoms.
The disease is cured if it is discovered in time, it is possible to exterminate the virus of the body, so it is possible to suppress contagion and prevent cancer.
September 30 is the World Hepatitis Day, which was first organized in 2004 by organizations representing the sick.
It aims to draw attention to the causes of chronic liver infections caused by the viruses and the importance of their early recognition.
Does it hurt less to those who believe in God?
According to the result of a recent investigation, religious faith has a calming effect that also relieved the death of the martyrs of Catholicism.
The scientists at the University of Oxford carried out an interesting experiment: they analyzed that religious belief in how it influences human pain - the British newspaper Telegraph reported.
In the framework of this unique experiment they applied electrical shock to 12 Catholic believers and to the same number of atheists, while all were looking at a painting of the Virgin Mary.
According to the results, Catholic believers were able to exclude most of their pain.
Thanks to the human brain's scanning technique, it was possible to verify that Catholic believers were able to activate that part of their brain that is responsible for the regulation of pain.
This experiment is the first in the series of research in which together with the academics also participate scientists, philosophers and theologians from the different departments of the University.
The analysis occurred as follows; they fixed a spitting instrument to the patient's left hand, which applied the electrical shock.
The researchers asked the participants of the experiment to look at two paintings; the Virgin Mary, the work of Sassoferrato of the 17th century and the Lady of the Armiño of Leonardo da Vinci of the 15th century.
The researchers had the hope that the spectacle of the Virgin Mary would cause a certain religious mood among the faithful, while they chose Leonardo's oil because it was not too different from the other, and they thought it had a reassuring effect.
The patients spent half an hour in an MRI scanner, receiving 20 electric shocks in four successive parts while watching the painting of religious theme or the other.
The Catholics said that when they looked at the Virgin Mary they felt "safe" as "protected people," they reassure themselves and in their heart peace reigned. "
When they looked at the picture of religious theme they felt 12 percent less pain than when they looked at Leonardo's work.
